[5] Canadian recalls
Date: Mon 2 Feb 2009
Source: 680News [edited]
<http://www.680news.com/news/headlines/more.jsp?content=20090202_075722_58204>


The Canadian Food Inspection Agency is expanding its recall of
products affected by the salmonella outbreak in a peanut factory in
the USA. At least 81 products sold in Canada contain ingredients from
that plant, and 39 of the products are made in Canada.

No illnesses have been reported in this country, but more than 500
people in the USA have fallen ill and 8 deaths are thought to be
linked to the salmonella outbreak.

Products recalled in Canada include various snack bars, mixed nuts
and cookies, bridge mix, kettle corn from a variety of companies
including Atkins, Arico, Clif Bar & Company and Nature's Path, with a
variety of UPC codes and best-before dates.

